cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.MA, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a routing protocol for wireless sensor networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the security aspects of the proposed protocol and how it can prevent attacks on the network. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper talks about clustering structure and how it can be used to design energy-efficient routing protocols for WSNs. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper proposes an autonomous sensor network that can be deployed randomly without human supervision, which falls under the domain of multiagent systems. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the mathematical analysis of the proposed protocol and how it can help in selecting suitable values of parameters for a particular WSN application, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
